%N A395356 a(n) = |A395355(n)| - |A395355(n-1)|.
%C A395356 Follow the spiral in A392177 and A392178 as it is populated with black and red knights; a(n) is the number of steps that the just-placed knight is ahead of the previously-placed knight.
%H A395356 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="/A395356/b395356.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000</a>
%H A395356 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="/A395356/a395356.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..91525</a>
%e A395356 The first few knights in the spiral are: 0th knight is a black knight at square 0, 1st knight is a red knight at square 1, 2nd knight is a black knight at square 2, 3rd is red knight at 3, 4th is black knight at 5, 5th is red knight at 4, etc. (see A395355). So a(4) = 5-3 = 2, a(5) = 4-5 = -1.
%Y A395356 Cf. A392177, A392178, A395355.
